originalText.text: I’ve seen numerous psychiatrists and therapists over the course of 25 years, without much relief. But Gwen is a game-changer. Her skill, experience, open-mindedness and authenticity allowed me to heal. She gave me a life I never thought I’d be able to lead, and now I don’t even need therapy anymore. Gwen Feldman is an exceptional person and professional. Highly recommend.

originalText.text: Working with Gwen has changed my life. It's been almost two years now and looking back at where we started and where my life and has gone since then. Not only is she an experienced professional, she is also patient, genuine, and caring. Give yourself a chance!

originalText.text: Gwen has been my therapist for a little over a year now and the growth I have accomplished with her guidance is something i'm truly proud of and very grateful for. She is an amazing soundboard and I truly feel heard and understood by her. Chatting with her once a week has helped immensely with relieving any anxieties I have about my own judgement and perceptions. I love her!

originalText.text: I’ve been seeing mental health professionals for close to a decade, but Gwen managed to fundamentally change my life in just a few months. Our most recent session was so profound that after a lifetime of struggling with my mental health I finally feel free. Since that day I’m the happiest I’ve ever been. The past two months have been the best of my life and I feel so happy and capable and grateful. It feels so surreal because after so long and so much work, I never thought I would reach this point. She saw what almost a dozen other professionals didn’t and has changed my life, my outlook on the world, and my view of myself forever. I cannot recommend her enough, especially if you have experienced trauma in your life or even think you might have. I feel resilient and I’m like I can handle whatever will come my way now and I’m so incredibly grateful I chose to work with Gwen.

originalText.text: Gwen is an incredible therapist. A friend referred me to her 5 years ago after a breakup and she quickly helped me understand my patterns and the reasons behind them. She listens and gives thoughtful advice that challenges you to self reflect in the best possible way. Her advice and support have been invaluable to me about everything from how communicate with my partner/now husband to be, to work and family and friend dynamics. I couldn't be more grateful to her!
